Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Gathering Spot in Atlanta, Georgia, emphasizing the importance of fighting for basic freedoms, particularly the right to vote. She discussed the challenges faced in Georgia, such as anti-voter laws that limit drop boxes and make it illegal to provide food and water to people waiting in line to vote. Harris also mentioned the harassment and intimidation of election workers, and the intentional drawing of unfair maps by politicians. She highlighted the need for free and fair elections and called for the passage of the Freedom to Vote Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Act. Harris thanked Representative Lucy McBath and Representative Nikema Williams for their work in Congress and acknowledged the historic achievements in Georgia's recent elections. She concluded by emphasizing the significance of people's voices and their ability to participate in shaping the future of their country.